title: Pallet
body:
As Part of #2649 a few ideas were collected how to iconize a cargo pallet.

Since this icon was hard to show without some 3D-tilt, @Templarian asked to split it into a seperate issue.

Some thoughts:
- What makes a pallet special is that you can move a plethora of differently shaped, but stackable objects at once on a common platform. Thats a  property reflected various other palet icons:   [1](https://previews.123rf.com/images/bobnevv/bobnevv1602/bobnevv160200070/52212689-pallet-icon-pallet-logo-pallet-symbol-cargo-icon-isolated-pallet-with-various-cargo-icon-minimal-des.jpg), [2](https://media.gettyimages.com/vectors/cardboard-boxes-on-a-wood-pallet-icon-vector-id466745620)
- Pyramids of equally shaped parcels can be found quite often and give a nice sense of symmetry while still giving a feeling of improvised packaging: [3](https://thenounproject.com/term/pallet/957605/).
- Icons with just one box on top of the pallet seem to drag the optical focus from the pallet to the load, representing more of a parcel/package then a pallet [4](https://thenounproject.com/term/pallet/214763/), [5](https://www.iconexperience.com/g_collection/icons/?icon=wooden_pallet_box), [6](https://www.iconexperience.com/o_collection/icons/?icon=wooden_pallet_box)
- The same holds true for very cubically packed pallets [7](https://glstock.com/graphic/4280014-cardboard-package-boxes-on-pallet-icon)

title: Change ownership
body:
I'm looking for an icon which symbolizes changing in ownership (of real estates). 
The idea of our customer is 2 people with tophat and interchange-arrow like in [account-switch](https://materialdesignicons.com/icon/account-switch). But I think 2 persons with tie or one person with tophat/tie like in [account-convert](https://materialdesignicons.com/icon/account-convert) would also work.
We currently use the  [account-switch](https://materialdesignicons.com/icon/account-switch)-icon which does not statisfy our customer, because the ownership-aspect is not strong enough.

These are just suggestions. Any other icon representing a switch/change of a powerful person (boss, admin, owner) is also highly appreciated.

Let me use this request to highlight the aspect, that we miss icons for people with authority like "boss" or "admin" in general.

title: Heads / Tails Coin
body:
There is a set of icons for all six sides of a six-sided die and for other types of dice. I think a good complement, for the sake of gaming, would be icons for the two sides of a coin: "heads" and "tails."

I'm not exactly sure what the icons should look like. "Heads" seems easy, there would just be a silhouette of a person's head inside a circle; e.g., an [American penny](http://lincolnpennies.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/lincoln_penny_obverse1.jpg). I guess for "tails" we could put something like a snake, monkey or [dragon](http://english.stackexchange.com/questions/154584/where-does-the-term-heads-or-tails-come-from), since those animals have prominent tails. Another idea would be to use the [same animal, front and back](http://kafelia.files.wordpress.com/2008/09/elephant_coin.jpg?w%20300%20h%20153).

title: Chef's Hat
body: I am looking for one or more icons for difficulty, more specifically recipe/cooking difficulty. This can be solved in many ways, for example by having multiple icons with filled and non-filled parts. title: Furigana
body:
![furiganaicon](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/430612/9367166/09bd34d4-46bc-11e5-97ed-ee3a59251036.png)

Japanese language uses small text over complex/obscure pictograms (kanjis) as an aid in the reading. Such an icon could be useful in contexts where that visual aid is necessary.

Furigana is sometimes signaled with the "" symbol (the one at the top of the image) too.
